# Diffusion constant in microns^2 / sec
D = 10

# Range of lengths in microns
L = np.logspace(0, 6, 100)

# Diffusion timescale
T = L**2 / D
In [14]:
# Make a plot in linear scale
plt.plot(L, T)
plt.xlabel('Length (micron)')
plt.ylabel('Time (sec)')
